WEBVTT

00:06.923 --> 00:08.025
Hey, hey, hey.

00:08.048 --> 00:09.402
Working hard, I see.

00:09.426 --> 00:10.736
Joe! God, Joe!

00:10.760 --> 00:12.770
- Joe, you're back.
- Yeah, I'm back.

00:12.887 --> 00:14.198
Wow!

00:14.222 --> 00:16.117
Will you look at this place?

00:16.140 --> 00:18.035
- Holy cow!
- Thanks.

00:18.059 --> 00:20.862
Um, yeah, I told you about...
What are you doing back?

00:20.979 --> 00:21.997
Charlie, where's your head?

00:22.021 --> 00:23.165
I gave you my schedule.

00:23.189 --> 00:25.324
I told you I was gonna be
here for a couple of weeks.

00:25.525 --> 00:26.627
It's a good thing too

00:26.651 --> 00:30.288
because I think we might
have a little problem.

00:31.406 --> 00:32.424
Certified mail?

00:32.448 --> 00:33.676
It's nothing to panic about,

00:33.700 --> 00:35.835
but that bastard Montgomery,

00:35.869 --> 00:38.087
he's finally decided
to sell the building.

00:38.747 --> 00:40.141
Oh, right. Right.

00:40.165 --> 00:42.935
He, uh, he mentioned
something about that.

00:42.959 --> 00:43.936
Yeah?

00:43.960 --> 00:47.013
Did he tell you about the buyer,
this Isley Financial Group?

00:47.380 --> 00:48.357
Not really.

00:48.381 --> 00:51.360
Uh, he pretty much just said
he was gonna accept the offer.

00:51.384 --> 00:52.528
Charlie, our lease
is up in June,

00:52.552 --> 00:54.645
so we gotta figure out
what their plans are.

00:55.263 --> 00:56.866
I-I don't know.

00:56.890 --> 01:00.453
Ah, you know, they probably
just want to jack up the rent

01:00.477 --> 01:02.496
and gouge us for whatever
they can get away with,

01:02.520 --> 01:05.239
but hey, we can handle it, right?
Huh?

01:05.440 --> 01:08.294
I mean, it wouldn't make sense
for them to boot us now.

01:08.318 --> 01:11.204
Look what you have
done with this place.

01:15.909 --> 01:18.044
Your old man would be proud.

